#
# ── KNOWN LIMITS AND HAZARDS ────────────────────────────────
# MAX_INSTRS = 32768: hard ceiling for RegIDs in any single function.
#   next_token is the current HWM at 190 blocks. Any function larger will
#   silently corrupt live[] or def_of[] before hitting a bounds check.
#   Long-term fix: growable def table. For now, assert r < MAX_INSTRS at
#   every worklist push rather than at the array access.
#   Add runtime check: if (r >= MAX_INSTRS) { fprintf(stderr, "[FATAL] RegID %u >= MAX_INSTRS\n", r); abort(); }
#
# DCE frees instructions in place. Any pass calling licm_build_def_block
#   after a destructive pass must call it again before use — def_of[]
#   entries for freed instructions are stale/dangling otherwise.
#   licm_build_def_block now clears def_of[] with memset(0) before rebuild.
#   If a third destructive pass is added, same pattern applies.
#
# Unsupported IR kinds (bridge coverage gaps as of Bridge 5):
#   kind  8 = ND_MUL     (multiply)
#   kind 19 = ND_LNOT    (logical not)
#   kind 20 = ND_BAND    (bitwise and)
#   kind 27 = ND_ADDR    (address-of)
#   kind 28 = ND_DEREF   (pointer deref)
#   kind 34 = ND_FOR     (for loop — entire stmt kind)
#   kind 48 = unknown stmt (likely ND_COMPOUND_ASSIGN or ND_SWITCH)
#   These produce NULL children that are skipped; affected functions
#   still reach zcc_ast_to_ir but produce incomplete IR.
#
# Build commands (Bridge 5 architecture):
#   gcc-only (bridge active):  gcc -O2 -w zcc_bridge_impl.c compiler_passes.c -o zcc_full -lm
#   ZCC self-host:             ./zcc_full zcc.c -o /tmp/zcc3.s
#   (ZCC parses zcc.c only; zcc_bridge_impl.c is gcc-only, never seen by ZCC)
#
# Bootstrap closure test (gcc → zcc_full → zcc3 → test):
#   ./zcc_full zcc.c -o /tmp/zcc3.s 2>/dev/null
#   gcc -c bootstrap_runtime.c -o /tmp/bootstrap_runtime.o
#   gcc /tmp/zcc3.s /tmp/bootstrap_runtime.o -o /tmp/zcc3 -lm
#   /tmp/zcc3 /tmp/t.c -o /tmp/t.s && gcc /tmp/t.s -o /tmp/t && /tmp/t  # expect exit 42
#   ZCC-generated zcc3.s references zcc_bridge_codegen_func, Compiler, offsetof; bootstrap_runtime.c
#   provides them. Bootstrap closed: zcc3 runs and compiles (e.g. int main(){return 42;} -> exit 42).
